message.content: One of the most significant events that happened in Barbados in the past 100 years is its attainment of independence from British colonial rule. On November 30, 1966, Barbados became an independent nation, ending over 300 years of British control. This event marked a crucial milestone in the country's history, as it gained full sovereignty and the ability to govern itself. Independence Day is now celebrated annually in Barbados to commemorate this significant event.
